::Savanna/Spitfire::

Savanna stayed back just in case of trouble.  Spitfire walked up to 
the Bounty Hunters. "Hello there.  If you fine gentlebots don't mind 
me taking just a few moments of your time, I was hoping you could 
spare a few moments and talk with  me a bit. I was just curios, would 
you like a hand on your mission, what ever it is?"  She smiled at 
then with the niced smiled she could muster.  Granted, she felt a bit 
low for doing this, but it is accomplished the job, she would do it. 
Well, with in reason.  She walked closer, her hood open and her 
tongue tasting the air.  The air tasted bad, to be honest with 
herself, but she kept on smiling.
